  "commentary": "With SPX at 6594.54 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-31B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+27B), dealers are in active hedging mode - buying the dip toward 6590 and ready to sell any push toward 6605, creating a tight 15-point trading range. The breakout regime with massive negative GEX (-64B total) means any break outside this 6590-6605 corridor will see dealers amplify the move rather than provide support. Watch for a break below the 6590 wall where dealers flip to aggressive buying, or above 6605 where they become heavy sellers - both scenarios trigger trending moves in a negative gamma environment.\n\nBottom line: expect violent whipsaws between 6590-6605 until one side breaks and triggers a bigger trending move.",
